# Array functions

We use simple array functions.

  * The function `arn` returns the array number of fields.
  * The function `ari` returns the array item at index i.
  * Both functions can take an optional field separator arg.

Array number of fields:

    arn() { a="$1"; x="{print NF}"; [ $# == 2 ] && awk -F "$2" "$x" <<< "$a" || awk "$x" <<< "$a" ; }

Array index:

    ari() { a="$1"; x="{print \$$2}"; [ $# == 3 ] && awk -F "$3" "$x" <<< "$a" || awk "$x" <<< "$a" ; }

Examples:

    arn "a b c" => 3
    arn "a-b-c" "-" => 3

    ari "a b c" 2 =>  "b"
    ari "a-b-c" 2 "-" =>  "b"    


    
    